summary.purpose: Provides four coloured jeep SVG icon generator functions (red, yellow, green, gray) conforming to the VehicleSvg signature for use as map markers and menu icons.
summary.problem_solved: Supplies the jeep vehicle type's state-specific icon variants so map and menu components can reflect real-time ignition and speed state visually.

exports.name: redJeepIcon
exports.description_one_line: Returns a red jeep SVG element with configurable size, site colour, CSS class, and viewBox context.

exports.name: yellowJeepIcon
exports.description_one_line: Returns a yellow jeep SVG element with configurable size, site colour, CSS class, and viewBox context.

exports.name: greenJeepIcon
exports.description_one_line: Returns a green jeep SVG element with configurable size, site colour, CSS class, and viewBox context.

exports.name: grayJeepIcon
exports.description_one_line: Returns a gray jeep SVG element with configurable size, site colour, CSS class, and viewBox context.

symbols.name: redJeepIcon
symbols.description_one_line: Returns a red jeep SVG element with configurable size, site colour, CSS class, and viewBox context.

params.name: width
params.description: Width attribute for the SVG element.

params.name: height
params.description: Height attribute for the SVG element.

params.name: siteColor
params.description: Fill colour for site-specific colour accents.

params.name: className
params.description: CSS class name applied to the SVG element.

params.name: viewBoxFor
params.description: Context identifier ('map_icon' or 'menu_icon').

returns.description: Red jeep icon SVG element. Red indicates ignition is off.

details.what_it_does: Generates a detailed jeep SVG icon in red, indicating ignition is off.

minimal_correct.title: Render a red jeep icon
minimal_correct.code:
import { redJeepIcon } from 'akeyless-assets-commons';

const icon = redJeepIcon('30', '30', '#FF0000', 'newIconCar', 'map_icon');
